name: Faces and Feelings That Never Were

metadata.name: Love is a Virus
metadata.description:
It is the invisible infiltrator,  
spreading through whispers  
and hot breath.  
A mouth on ours.  
Fingertips against skin.

Infecting us before we know it.  
Ravaging us without remorse.  
Pouring out of every pore  
until it coats us  
for all to see.  
Leaving its slick residue  
in our bones, our blood,  
our hearts,  
even after itâ€™s had its way with us  
and left us mangled.  
Changed.  
Strengthened.

The only disparity:  
as soon as we recover  
from the embrace of that  
sweet sickness,  
we long for infection to return.

___

By Cosmic Camera, 2023
